volumeInfo.title: Roving Mars
volumeInfo.subtitle: Spirit, Opportunity, and the Exploration of the Red Planet
volumeInfo.description: Combining the journey of a young scientist with the history of NASA's Mars space program, Roving Mars offers a dramatic account of one of the most amazing adventures of our time. In a conversational and compelling voice, Squyres describes how the MER mission was born, and discusses the politics, mistakes, and confusion that threatened the mission. He leads us through the exhausting and exhilarating race to get the rovers to the launchpad in time. And, finally, he relates the amazing story of Spirit's and Opportunity's journeys to Mars and what has been found there.
